parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The instability of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to fishtail or sway uncontrollably, making it difficult to maintain control, especially at high speeds, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The rear end of the vehicle sways or fishtails
especially on icy or snowy roads
and sometimes even on dry roads with bumps or potholes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension and steering components can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, making it difficult to steer, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side
the steering feels loose or unstable
and the front tires wear unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel bearings can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake, making it difficult to control, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or shakes
especially at high speeds
and the wheel bearings make a grinding or growling noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission components can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, making it difficult to shift gears, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle stalls or hesitates when shifting gears
and the transmission makes a grinding or whining noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the Takata airbag recall may lead to a delay in the repair, putting the driver and passengers at risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are not available for repair
dealer advises to not allow passengers to ride in the front passenger seat
delay in repair
and lack of communication from the manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in the repair of the Takata airbag recall may lead to a risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but repair is delayed
dealer advises to not allow passengers to ride in the front passenger seat
and lack of communication from the manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of communication from the manufacturer and dealerships regarding the Takata airbag recall may lead to frustration and anxiety for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Lack of communication from the manufacturer and dealerships
difficulty in scheduling repairs
and uncertainty about the availability of parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle position sensor can cause the accelerator pedal to become unresponsive, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels soft or spongy
the accelerator pedal sticks to the floor
the accelerator pedal does not return to its normal position
the accelerator pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the accelerator pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The cruise control turns off unexpectedly
the cruise control accelerates or decelerates rapidly
the vehicle surges or pulses when descending hills
the cruise control does not engage or disengage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent loss of power can cause the vehicle to stall or lose acceleration, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or acceleration
the engine light comes on
the vehicle stalls or hesitates
the accelerator pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake fluid leaks
brake lines are corroded
brake warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ineffective repair of the brake lines can lead to continued corrosion and failure, causing the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake fluid leaks
brake lines are corroded
brake warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose control, making it difficult to stop or maneuver, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: ABS system engages unnecessarily
vehicle loses control
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake fluid leaks
brake lines are corroded
brake warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The warping of the brake pads can cause the brake pedal to vibrate or pulsate, making it difficult to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal vibrates or pulsates
brake pads are warped
brake fluid leaks
brake lines are corroded
brake warning light is illuminated.
